OL,3,CWarnings to parents over banned
OL,4,CAmerican sweets posing 'serious health
OL,5,Crisks'
OL,7,F"Retailers must take responsibility to
OL,8,Fensure compliance, and parents need to
OL,9,Fbe vigilant in checking labels to
OL,10,Fprotect their children from potential
OL,11,Fharm.
OL,13,F"Importers, by law, have to re-label
OL,14,Fproducts with a UK/GB address. If
OL,15,Fthere is any problem with the food,
OL,16,Fcustomers and Trading Standards may
OL,17,Fneed to contact a legally responsible
OL,18,Fperson in this country. If food does
OL,19,Fnot have a UK/GB address on the label,
OL,20,Fwe would advise for them not to buy
OL,21,Fit."
